1. Create a distribution point

-Click on the Start button and open Go to Start and open Group Policy Management (or press Win+R  , then type  gpmc.msc, then press Enter)
-Expand Forest (your forest) > Domains (your domain)
-Сlick on you domain and looking for a previously installed policy (eg "Install HES application v.3.3.10")
-Right-click and select "Edit"

-Expand Computer Configuration > Policies > Software Settings
Right-clickon the package with the desired name (for example, “Install THIS application.” Next, “All Tasks” - "Remove..."
- In the window that appears, leave the default feature that allows you to "Immediately uninstall the software  from users and computers"
